VL  - 161
IS  - 2
SP  - 101
EP  - 109
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/04/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jeconom.2010.04.010
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304407610002526
KW  - Real-time analysis
KW  - Data revisions
AB  - Policy makers must base their decisions on preliminary and partially revised data of varying reliability. Realistic modeling of data revisions is required to guide decision makers in their assessment of current and future conditions. This paper provides a new framework with which to model data revisions. Recent empirical work suggests that measurement errors typically have much more complex dynamics than existing models of data revisions allow. This paper describes a state-space model that allows for richer dynamics in these measurement errors, including the noise, news and spillover effects documented in this literature. We also show how to relax the common assumption that “true” values are observed after a few revisions. The result is a unified and flexible framework that allows for more realistic data revision properties, and allows the use of standard methods for optimal real-time estimation of trends and cycles. We illustrate the application of this framework with real-time data on US real output growth.
ER  - 

